__data__.text: On January 15, 2024, claim number CLM-2024-00789-AUTO was filed by policyholder Sarah Mitchell for her 2022 Honda Accord. A multi-vehicle collision occurred at the intersection of Maple Avenue and 5th Street in Downtown Seattle at 09:23:45 AM, resulting in significant property damage and minor injuries. The total estimated claim value is $47,850, covering vehicle repairs and medical expenses.

metadata.involved_parties: Sarah Mitchell, Robert Chen, Seattle Police Department, Officer James Wilson
Sarah Mitchell, Robert Chen, Seattle Police Department, Officer James Wilson

__data__.text: On January 15, 2024, at 09:23:45 AM, a collision occurred at the intersection of Maple Avenue and 5th Street in Seattle, involving Sarah Mitchell and Robert Chen. Mitchell, traveling northbound, was struck on the driver's side by Chen's eastbound Toyota Camry, which entered the intersection against a red light. The impact caused significant damage to Mitchell's Honda Accord and resulted in her experiencing neck pain and dizziness. No financial amounts or costs were mentioned in the details provided.

metadata.involved_parties: Seattle Fire Department, Medic Unit 47, Paramedic Jennifer Ross, Officer James Wilson, Sarah Mitchell
Seattle Fire Department, Medic Unit 47, Paramedic Jennifer Ross, Officer James Wilson, Sarah Mitchell

__data__.text: On January 15, 2024, at 09:31:22 AM, first responders from the Seattle Fire Department and Medic Unit 47 arrived at a collision scene. Paramedic Jennifer Ross assessed the injured party, Sarah Mitchell, who reported significant neck stiffness and a headache. Officer James Wilson secured the intersection, and evidence revealed that Chen's vehicle had a brake warning light active for 12 days prior to the incident. Property damage estimates totaled $47,850, including $18,400 for Mitchell's vehicle and $22,300 for Chen's vehicle.

metadata.involved_parties: Dr. Michael Patterson, Sarah Mitchell, Claims Adjuster Linda Martinez, Police Investigation Unit
Dr. Michael Patterson, Sarah Mitchell, Claims Adjuster Linda Martinez, Police Investigation Unit

__data__.text: On January 15, 2024, at 14:45:18, Dr. Michael Patterson examined Mitchell at Seattle Medical Center following her ambulance transport for a whiplash injury and concussion. Claims Adjuster Linda Martinez conducted a phone interview with Mitchell to document the incident, confirming liability assigned to Robert Chen. The total estimated claim value is $47,850, comprising $44,010 for vehicle damage and $3,840 for medical expenses.

metadata.header: Event 4: Vehicle Inspection and Repair Assessment
metadata.involved_parties: Premier Auto Body Shop, Certified Inspector Thomas Blake, Sarah Mitchell, Progressive Insurance Adjuster

__data__.text: On January 16, 2024, at 10:30 AM, Mitchell's 2022 Honda Accord was inspected at Premier Auto Body Shop by Certified Inspector Thomas Blake. The inspection revealed extensive structural damage requiring complete replacement of several components, with total parts costs estimated at $12,450. Labor costs were calculated at $8,312.50 for 87.5 hours of work. Third-party appraiser David Richardson confirmed the repair estimates and structural integrity restoration in his report (IAA-2024-1567). Additional costs included $890 for equipment rental and $2,340 for paint materials.

metadata.header: Event 5: Medical Follow-up and Physical Therapy
metadata.involved_parties: Dr. Michael Patterson, Sarah Mitchell, Physical Therapist Amanda Chen, Seattle Rehabilitation Center

__data__.text: On January 22, 2024, Mitchell attended a follow-up appointment with Dr. Michael Patterson at Seattle Medical Center, revealing cervical spine tenderness and a pain level decrease from six to four. Dr. Patterson prescribed a 12-session physical therapy program at Seattle Rehabilitation Center, led by Physical Therapist Amanda Chen. The total estimated medical treatment costs amount to $3,840, fully covered under Mitchell's insurance policy.

metadata.involved_parties: Marcus Thompson, Seattle Police Department, Traffic Engineer Dr. Susan Miller, Video Forensics Team
Marcus Thompson, Seattle Police Department, Traffic Engineer Dr. Susan Miller, Video Forensics Team

__data__.text: On January 15, 2024, at 11:45 AM, a collision occurred involving Chen's vehicle, which entered an intersection against a red signal. Witness Marcus Thompson observed the incident and provided a sworn statement to the Seattle Police Department. Traffic Engineer Dr. Susan Miller confirmed the traffic signal was functioning correctly, while the Video Forensics Team documented that Chen's vehicle violated the red light by 2.277 seconds. No financial amounts were mentioned in the report.

metadata.involved_parties: Progressive Auto Insurance, Claims Adjuster Linda Martinez, Sarah Mitchell, Finance Department
Progressive Auto Insurance, Claims Adjuster Linda Martinez, Sarah Mitchell, Finance Department

__data__.text: On January 17, 2024, at 09:00 AM, Progressive Auto Insurance Claims Adjuster Linda Martinez completed a financial assessment for claim file CLM-2024-00789-AUTO. The assessment detailed vehicle damage costs of $44,010 and medical expenses of $3,840, totaling a claim value of $47,850. Mitchell's policy provides comprehensive coverage with a $500 deductible, resulting in a net payment of $43,510 for vehicle costs and $3,840 paid directly to medical providers.

metadata.involved_parties: Seattle Police Department, Officer James Wilson, Robert Chen, Chen's Insurance - State Farm, Legal Department
Seattle Police Department, Officer James Wilson, Robert Chen, Chen's Insurance - State Farm, Legal Department

__data__.text: On January 18, 2024, at 13:30:00, the Seattle Police Department issued a traffic citation to Robert Chen for failing to obey a traffic control device. State Farm Insurance accepted liability for the incident, confirming 100% fault for damages incurred by Sarah Mitchell, including vehicle damage and medical expenses, totaling $500 in fines. Claims Representative Michael Torres managed the claim, while Progressive Auto Insurance's Legal Department, represented by Patricia Anderson, authorized claims payment processing.

__data__.text: Claim ID CLM-2024-00789-AUTO was resolved on February 5, 2024, for policyholder Sarah Mitchell regarding her vehicle. The incident involved an auto accident that occurred prior to the claim date. The total estimated claim value is $47,850, covering vehicle damage and medical expenses.
